message.content:
cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with predicting saliency maps on omnidirectional images using deep learning techniques. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel approach using generative adversarial imitation learning (GAIL) to predict saliency of head fixations on ODIs. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses deep reinforcement learning (DRL) to predict head fixations of one subject and multi-stream DRL to yield head fixations of different subjects. 
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible category as the paper discusses the establishment of a dataset for attention on ODIs and the findings related to head fixations of subjects. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with predicting saliency maps on omnidirectional images, which is a multimedia application.
